news_header: Several companies are set to report earnings on January 28, 2025, with varying forecasts and performance trends.
news_original_title: After-Hours Earnings Report for January 28, 2025 :  SYK, SBUX, CB, PKG, MANH, FFIV, LOGI, RNR, BXP, HLI, QRVO, UMBF
news_text: On January 28, 2025, multiple companies will announce their earnings. Stryker Corporation (SYK) expects $3.87 EPS, an 11.85% increase from last year. Starbucks Corporation (SBUX) anticipates $0.66 EPS, a 26.67% decrease. Chubb Limited (CB) forecasts $5.46 EPS, down 34.22%. Packaging Corporation of America (PKG) expects $2.51 EPS, an increase of 17.84%. Manhattan Associates, Inc. (MANH) predicts $0.75 EPS, a decrease of 3.85%. F5, Inc. (FFIV) expects $2.59 EPS, down 2.63%. Logitech International S.A. (LOGI) anticipates $1.23 EPS, a decrease of 13.99%. RenaissanceRe Holdings Ltd. (RNR) forecasts $7.61 EPS, down 35.34%. BXP, Inc. (BXP) expects $1.79 EPS, a decrease of 1.65%. Houlihan Lokey, Inc. (HLI) anticipates $1.51 EPS, an increase of 23.77%. Qorvo, Inc. (QRVO) expects $0.87 EPS, down 53.97%. UMB Financial Corporation (UMBF) forecasts $2.30 EPS, an increase of 0.44%. Zacks Investment Research provides insights on price-to-earnings ratios indicating growth potential.
